'''[[Sailing]]''' (also called [[yachting]]) at the '''[[1980 Summer Olympics]]''' was represented by six events. They were all held at the ''[[Pirita]] Yachting Centre'', situated in [[Tallinn Bay]], on the [[Baltic Sea]] in [[Tallinn]]. The schedule started on July 22 and ended on August 1.
